verbose_text: Because cytoplasmic in-sulin can overlap with the nuclei of non beta cells, we sought to more definitively determine whether beta cell nuclei showed higher levels of pSMAD5; indeed, insulin and Nkx6.1 double positive cells contained higher levels of pSMAD5 in CF compared with non CF beta cells (2-way ANOVA with Tukey HSD, p = 5.6e-3; XREF_FIG).
